                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "mmm I don't think so.\nLasterInsertId() should be client aware and fully atomic. That's the main difference between lastInsertId() and some kind of select(max(id)) from table.\n\nPerhaps I'm wrong, I dont know all RDBMs",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
